---
title: Availability inside the cluster is not a backup
config:
  layout: elk
---
flowchart LR
  accTitle: Longhorn, Kopiur, and Barman failure domains
  accDescr: Longhorn and CSI snapshots remain inside Kubernetes. Kopiur copies application data to RustFS and restores replacement PVCs before binding. CloudNativePG uses a separate Barman bucket.

  subgraph CLUSTER["TALOS CLUSTER"]
    direction TB
    APP["`Application pod
    reads and writes`"]
    PVC["`Longhorn PVC
    live block storage`"]
    SNAP["`CSI snapshot
    point-in-time source`"]
    REPLACE["`Replacement PVC
    Pending`"]
    MOVER["`Kopiur restore mover
    hydrates volume`"]
    BOUND["`PVC Bound with data
    application may start`"]
    CNPG["`CloudNativePG
    database and WAL`"]
    APP app@--> PVC
    PVC snapshot@--> SNAP
    REPLACE restore1@--> MOVER
    MOVER restore2@--> BOUND
  end

  subgraph OFFCLUSTER["OUTSIDE KUBERNETES"]
    direction TB
    RUSTFS["`TrueNAS / RustFS
    separate host boundary`"]
    KOPIA["`Kopia bucket
    application snapshots`"]
    BARMAN["`postgres-backups bucket
    base backup and WAL`"]
    RUSTFS ~~~ KOPIA
    KOPIA ~~~ BARMAN
  end

  SNAP backup@-- "Kopia mover" --> KOPIA
  KOPIA hydrate@-- "restore" --> MOVER
  CNPG database@-- "Barman" --> BARMAN

  classDef workload fill:#fde8e8,stroke:#dc8c8c,color:#17212b
  classDef runtime fill:#dff4f6,stroke:#70bcc4,color:#17212b
  classDef restore fill:#e1f3e8,stroke:#7bc397,color:#17212b
  classDef external fill:#fff3df,stroke:#d8ad55,color:#17212b
  class APP workload
  class PVC,SNAP,CNPG runtime
  class REPLACE,MOVER,BOUND restore
  class RUSTFS,KOPIA,BARMAN external

  app@{ animation: fast }
  snapshot@{ animation: fast }
  backup@{ animation: slow }
  hydrate@{ animation: slow }
  restore1@{ animation: fast }
  restore2@{ animation: fast }
  database@{ animation: slow }
